body:
We need a way to associate ARM template files with a language ID separate from the current JSON language.  Unfortunately, the existing firstLine filter for languages doesn't suffice for ARM templates (or for any other sub-JSON support). ARM template files are .json files and generally look like this:
 
{
    "$schema": "http://schema.management.azure.com/schemas/2015-01-01/deploymentTemplate.json#",
    "contentVersion": "1.0.0.0",
    "parameters": {
 
The $schema value is the key to knowing if it’s an ARM template (technically it could be anywhere in the file although it’s usually at the top like this).  So we need a way to check further into the file than the first line.  Thanks!
